node.text:
sorry for the serious post but this has been on my mind
i have been doing ballet since i was 3 years old. i went to a strict ballet academy where every other student was as thin as a toothpick. i wasn't blessed with a fast metabolism or "thin genes". during the 16 years that i trained there, i was constantly told to lose weight or i'd never get anywhere with ballet. i wasn't allowed to perform certain roles because they wouldn't allow me on stage in a tutu, even after being told i was capable of doing the part. at that time, i was only 115 pounds so i never really thought of myself as overweight. for years i struggled with serious eating disorders which led me to no avail. i recently did a photoshoot with balletzaida; he made me feel beautiful. something i haven't felt in years. if only my ballet instructors could see who I've become.. because when they said "you can't", i said "watch me". the point of me saying all this is because a lot of my followers are aspiring, young dancers. i know very well how hard it is, as a dancer, to look in the mirror and actually be happy with what you see. YOU are beautiful and perfect the way you are; do not let anyone tell you that you cannot pursue your passion
You are beautiful through and through my dear. Sometimes people telling us we can't do something is just the push we need to do that very thing. Never doubt you can.
